0a%20good%20idea%20to%20do%20it%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20consider%20inheritances%20and%20money%20from%20families%20a%20gift%20of%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20intention%20is%20to%20give%20that%20money%20to%20family%20as%20an%20inheritance%2C%20you%20probably%20want%20that%20money%20put%20to%20best%20use%20for%20the%20maximum%20amount%20of%20time%20that%20creates%20the%20most%20peace%20of%20mind%20for%20everybody%20involved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20max%20amount%20that%20can%20be%20gifted%20each%20year%20tax-free%20is%20%2418%2C000%20for%20an%20individual%20or%20%2436%2C000%20for%20a%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrucker%20said%20he%20thinks%20he's%20seeing%20this%20wealth%20transfer%20happen%20more%20often%20in%20part%20because%20the%20current%20estate%20tax%20exemption%20put%20in%20place%20by%20the%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act%20of%202017%20is%20set%20to%20expire%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-estate-tax%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestate%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20currently%20ranges%20from%2018%25%20to%2040%25%20and%20kicks%20in%20for%20assets%20passed%20on%20that%20are%20above%20%2413.61%20million.%20That%20threshold%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%20be%20cut%20in%20half%20in%202026%2C%20meaning%20the%20estate%20tax%20would%20apply%20to%20more%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20are%20not%20impacted%20by%20the%20estate%20tax%2C%20Drucker%20said%20hearing%20about%20the%20exemption%20expiring%20has%20inspired%20some%20people%20to%20start%20thinking%20more%20about%20the%20best%20way%20to%20pass%20on%20their%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20Drucker%20cautions%20against%20is%20giving%20your%20kids%20money%20in%20a%20way%20that%20might%20up%20their%20standard%20of%20living%20to%20a%20level%20they%20can't%20actually%20sustain.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20parents%20help%20with%20a%20down%20payment%20that%20allows%20the%20recipients%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20and%20live%20in%20a%20neighborhood%20that%20they%20may%20not%20actually%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20gift%20recipients%20should%20use%20the%20money%20to%20better%20plan%20their%20finances%20rather%20than%20radically%20upscaling%20their%20standard%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrucker%20and%20Daigle%20both%20said%20that%20if%20parents%20determine%20they%20are%20financially%20secure%20and%20able%20to%20help%20their%20adult%20children%20financially%2C%20then%20it%20should%20start%20with%20a%20conversation%20about%20what%20that%20might%20look%20like%20and%20what%20would%20be%20best%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20all%20starts%20with%20the%20parents%20or%20the%20older%20family%20members%20really%20knowing%20enough%20about%20their%20own%20financial%20situation%2C%20having%20clarity%20around%20their%20spending%20needs%2C%20their%20income%2C%20their%20assets%2C%20to%20then%20be%20able%20to%20decide%20'what's%20the%20purpose%20of%20all%20this%20money%3F%20What%20do%20I%20want%20to%20do%3F'%26quot%3B%20Drucker%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20all%20starts%20with%20that%20conversation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20boomer%20who%20has%20an%20opinion%20about%20passing%20along%20wealth%20to%20offspring%2C%20or%20a%20millennial%20who%20is%20the%20recipient%20of%20earlier%20parental%20help%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-waiting-pass-inheritance-wealth-transfer-millennials-need-it-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%