t%3Bvacuum%20gun%26quot%3B%20to%20shoot%20nets%20at%20oncoming%20drones%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20system%20has%20already%20been%20tested%20and%20that%20preliminary%20orders%20had%20been%20placed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noted%20that%20the%20developers%20had%20been%20inspired%20by%20the%20use%20of%20barrage%20balloons%20in%20WWI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarrage%20balloons%20were%20first%20used%20in%20WWI%2C%20but%20they%20played%20a%20particularly%20key%20role%20in%20Britain's%20defenses%20during%20WWII.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iwm.org.uk%2Fcollections%2Fitem%2Fobject%2F15503%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFirst%2520used%2520during%2520the%2520First%2C1941%25202%252C748%2520were%2520in%2520use.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELondon's%20Imperial%20War%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Britain%20had%202%2C748%20barrage%20balloons%20in%20use%20by%20September%201941.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20also%20crucial%20during%20the%20D-Day%20landings%20on%20June%206%2C%201944%2C%20providing%20protection%20to%20Allied%20soldiers%20and%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20balloons%20forced%20German%20aircraft%20to%20fly%20at%20higher%20altitudes%2C%20making%20their%20targets%20more%20difficult%20to%20strike%20as%20well%20as%20making%20them%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20antiaircraft%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cables%20that%20anchored%20the%20balloons%20to%20the%20ground%20could%20also%20pose%20a%20serious%20risk%20to%20any%20aircraft%20attempting%20to%20fly%20through%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20balloons%20offered%20%26quot%3Ba%20vital%20means%20of%20defence%20against%20the%20%5BGerman%5D%20Luftwaffe%20as%20their%20trailing%20metal%20cables%20would%20severely%20damage%20or%20destroy%20any%20aircraft%20which%20touched%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20report%20published%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frafa.org.uk%2Fblog%2F2020%2F10%2F13%2Fbarrage-balloons-in-the-second-world-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoyal%20Air%20Forces%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAttackers%20attempting%20to%20shoot%20down%20a%20balloon%20could%20be%20caught%20in%20an%20explosion%20of%20the%20hydrogen%20used%20to%20get%20them%20airborne%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20convoy%20of%20merchantmen%20and%20colliers%20protected%20by%20warships%20of%20the%20Royal%20Navy%20and%20anti%20aircraft%20barrage%20balloons%20assemble%20off%20the%20North%20West%20Coast%20of%20England%20ready%20to%20depart%20on%2017th%20July%201942.%20(Photo%20by%20Central%20Press%2FHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668aa6a0268f62ba18a7ee67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBarrage%20balloons%20protect%20a%20convoy%20of%20ships%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20England%2C%20July%2017%2C%201942%3Cp%3ECentral%20Press%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Russia%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20continued%20to%20target%20Russian%20energy%20infrastructure%20and%20airbases%20with%20long-range%20drone%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELt.%20Gen.%20Kyrylo%20Budanov%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Defense%20Intelligence%20Directorate%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20told%20The%20War%20Zone%20in%20June%20that%20Ukrainian%20forces%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-mass-attack-russian-airbase-70-drones-budanov-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%2070%20drones%20in%20a%20strike%20on%20Morozovsk%20airbase%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Russia's%20Rostov%20region%2C%20almost%20200%20miles%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20security%20source%20told%20Sky%20News%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20attack%20was%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bsustained%20campaign%20to%20degrade%20the%20Russian%20Air%20Force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20in%20June%2C