arget%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recession%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20according%20to%20the%20most%20bearish%20strategist%20on%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Berezin%2C%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20BCA%20Research%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20note%20that%20a%20recession%20will%20hit%20the%20US%20economy%20later%20this%20year%20or%20in%20early%202025%2C%20and%20the%20downturn%20will%20send%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20tumbling%20to%203%2C750.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20consensus%20soft-landing%20narrative%20is%20wrong.%20The%20US%20will%20fall%20into%20a%20recession%20in%20late%202024%20or%20early%202025.%20Growth%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20will%20also%20slow%20sharply%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Berezin's%20bearish%20outlook%20is%20based%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20Fed%20will%20%26quot%3Bdrag%20its%20feet%26quot%3B%20in%20cutting%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20the%20central%20bank%20will%20only%20meaningfully%20loosen%20financial%20conditions%20until%20a%20recession%20is%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20it%20will%20be%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerezin%20highlighted%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20weakening%20as%20job%20openings%20decline%20materially%20from%20their%20post-pandemic%20peak.%20An%20ongoing%20decline%20in%20the%20quits%20rate%2C%20hiring%20rate%2C%20and%20recent%20downward%20revisions%20to%20the%20April%20and%20May%20jobs%20report%20also%20point%20to%20a%20slowing%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwo%20years%20ago%2C%20workers%20who%20lost%20their%20jobs%20could%20simply%20walk%20across%20the%20street%20to%20find%20new%20work.%20That%20has%20become%20increasingly%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-today-dovish-june-jobs-report-bond-yields-decline-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%20jobs%20report%20showed%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20ticking%20higher%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%204.1%25%20from%204.0%25%2C%20yet%20another%20sign%20of%20some%20mild%20weakness%20in%20the%20jobs%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20unemployment%20could%20ultimately%20lead%20to%20consumers%20reducing%20their%20spending%20to%20build%20up%20their%20%26quot%3Bprecautionary%20savings%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said%2C%20and%20that%20will%20happen%20as%20consumers'%20ability%20to%20borrow%20money%20narrows%20due%20to%20rising%20delinquency%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20a%20negative%20feedback%20loop%20will%20develop%20in%20the%20broader%20economy%2C%20which%20will%20send%20the%20stock%20market%20reeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20little%20accumulated%20savings%20to%20draw%20on%20and%20credit%20availability%20becoming%20more%20constrained%2C%20many%20households%20will%20have%20little%20choice%20but%20to%20curb%20spending.%20Decreased%20spending%20will%20lead%20to%20less%20hiring.%20Rising%20unemployment%20will%20curb%20income%20growth%2C%20leading%20to%20less%20spending%20and%20even%20higher%20unemployment%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20perhaps%20most%20importantly%2C%20the%20Fed's%20plan%20to%20blunt%20any%20economic%20decline%20via%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20simply%20won't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20important%20to%20recognize%20that%20what%20matters%20for%20the%20economy%20is%20not%20the%20fed%20funds%20rate%20per%20se%2C%20but%20the%20interest%20rate%20that%20households%20and%20businesses%20actually%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20average%20mortgage%20rate%20paid%20by%20consumers%20is%20around%204%25%2C%20compared%20to%20current%20mortgage%20rates%20of%20around%207%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20even%20if%20the%20Fed%20cuts%20interest%20rates%20and%20mortgage%20rates%20decline%2C%20%3Ca%20hr